claim.claim-text:
1. A process for installation of a lockbolt to fasten together an assembly of at least two parts having an interface therebetween containing a viscous fluid such as adhesive or sealant, comprising: 
inserting a lockbolt into aligned fastener holes through said two parts; 
exerting a pulling force of a predetermined intermediate magnitude on a pintail of said lockbolt and reacting said pulling force against opposite sides of said assembly to exert a compressive force on said assembly to squeeze said fluid out of said interface; 
maintaining said pulling force at said intermediate magnitude for a precisely timed dwell period based on an optimal period; 
after said dwell period, increasing said pulling force while simultaneously swaging a collar into a threaded portion of said lockbolt to secure said collar on said lockbolt and secure said lockbolt in a state of tension in said hole in said assembly; and 
thereafter continuing to increase said pulling force until said pintail breaks off said lockbolt.

4. A process as defined in claim 2, wherein: 
said dwelt period for said lockbolt is within 0.10 seconds of said optimal period; 
whereby fastener preload and fastener installation rate are optimized for the particular fastener and interfacial fluid used in said assembly.

7. A system for installation of a lockbolt in a fastener hole in an assembly of at least two parts having an interface therebetween containing a viscous fluid such as adhesive or sealant, said installation including inserting a lockbolt into a fastener hole through said parts; pulling on a pintail of said lockbolt with a force of a predetermined intermediate magnitude and reacting said pulling force against opposite sides of said assembly to exert a compressive force on said assembly to squeeze said fluid out of said interface; maintaining said pulling force at said intermediate magnitude for a precisely timed dwell period based on an optimal period; increasing said pulling force after said dwell period, while simultaneously swaging a collar into a threaded portion of said lockbolt to secure said collar on said lockbolt and secure said lockbolt in a state of tension in said hole in said assembly; and thereafter continuing to increase said pulling force and continue said collar swaging until said pintail breaks off said lockbolt; said system comprising: 
a puller tool having grippers for gripping said lockbolt pintail and for pulling on said lockbolt in said fastener hole and pushing said collar against said assembly to exert said compressive force on said assembly; 
a power unit for delivering a source of pressurized fluid to said tool; 
fluid passage channels from said power unit said tool for conveying fluid under pressure from said power unit to said tool; 
a cylinder in said tool and a piston in said cylinder operable under influence of pressurized hydraulic fluid controlled by said power unit to exert said pulling force on said lockbolt; 
a pressure reduction circuit in said power unit for reducing pressure in said pressurized fluid delivered through said fluid passage channels to said tool during said dwell period for a predetermined duration; 
a dwell circuit for controlling said duration of said dwell period.

12. A lockbolt installation system as defined in claim 10, wherein: 
said tool includes an air-over-oil canister for pressurizing said hydraulic fluid with air pressure from an air pressure source to power said piston; 
said pressure regulator is in an air pressure line to said canister in said tool; 
said timer is part of a time delay relay and said valve is operated by said time delay relay; and 
said valve is in a by-pass air line around said pressure regulator to allow full air pressure from said air pressure source to enter said canister to increase said hydraulic fluid pressure after said timer times out.
